<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Software on Edge AI Foundation Badge</title><link>https://lyndlabs.github.io/Edge-AI-Badge-Docs/software/</link><description>Recent content in Software on Edge AI Foundation Badge</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><copyright>Copyright (c) 2020-2026 Thulite</copyright><lastBuildDate>Tue, 09 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://lyndlabs.github.io/Edge-AI-Badge-Docs/software/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Programming the Badge</title><link>https://lyndlabs.github.io/Edge-AI-Badge-Docs/software/flashing/</link><pubDate>Tue, 09 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://lyndlabs.github.io/Edge-AI-Badge-Docs/software/flashing/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;If you have an unprogrammed badge, there&amp;rsquo;s only 4 steps to upload our pre-built firmware!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;

&lt;a class="link link--text" href="https://github.com/LyndLabs/Edge-AI-Badge-Docs/raw/main/edge-ai-badge/assets/v0.0_Edge-AI_Firmware.bin" rel="external"&gt;Download the pre-built firmware file&lt;/a&gt; on your computer.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Put your badge in 

&lt;a class="link link--text" href=""&gt;programming mode&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Choose your programming method (

&lt;a class="link link--text" href=""&gt;Chrome&lt;/a&gt; / 

&lt;a class="link link--text" href=""&gt;Command-Line&lt;/a&gt;).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;

&lt;a class="link link--text" href=""&gt;Reset your badge&lt;/a&gt;, and enjoy!&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;

